AT LEAST 13 people were killed after falling into a hole during a wedding ceremony in the northern Indian state of Uttar Pradesh. According to police, the victims, all women and children, were sitting on a metal slab covering the hole when it collapsed under their weight. Two more people were injured in the accident, that took place in Kushinagar district. According to the BBC, prime minister Narendra Modi called the deaths “heart-wrenching”. The tragedy occurred on Wednesday evening during the traditional “haldi” ceremony, in which relatives apply turmeric paste to the bride and groom’s faces as a sign of prosperity. When the slab collapsed, other guests rushed to save the victims and transport them to a nearby hospital. While 11 people were declared dead on the scene, two others died later during treatment, according to police. The publication reports that Uttar Pradesh chief minister Yogi Adityanath has asked district authorities to assist families of the victims while district magistrate S Rajalingam said they would be paid compensation.